# Phase 23 — Cloudflare Final Operating Model

## Objective

Produce the final, long-term operating model for safe Cloudflare runtime governance within the ZeaZ Platform. This phase synthesizes all prior governance phases (10–22) into a unified RACI, governance runbook, change lifecycle, and quarterly review framework that ensures the governance system remains maintainable long-term.

This phase must NOT deploy, apply, destroy, or mutate Cloudflare. It is the final documentation layer in this governance sequence.

---

## Branch Name

```
fix/cloudflare-final-operating-model
```

## Commit Message

```
docs(cloudflare): add final operating model
```

---

## Scope

- Create the final operating model overview doc
- Create RACI ownership matrix
- Create governance runbook
- Create quarterly review template
- Create runtime governance summary (links all phases 10–23)
- Update `infra/cloudflare/README.md` with Phase 23 entry and finalize the phase table

---

## Non-Goals

- Do NOT run `wrangler deploy`, `terraform apply`, `tofu apply`, or any Cloudflare write
- Do NOT print, log, or commit secrets, credentials, or tokens
- Do NOT start or restart any services
- Do NOT edit `/etc/cloudflared/config.yml`
- Do NOT modify files outside Phase 23 scope

---

## Safety Rules

1. All RACI entries must use role names — not real personal information or email addresses
2. No executable mutating commands in the runbook
3. All docs must clearly separate: governance area | owner | process | cadence | evidence required
4. Runbook must not include commands that deploy, apply, or delete live Cloudflare resources
5. Quarterly review template must include a column for "governance gaps found"
6. Never print secrets or credentials in any example

