## Operating Model Lifecycle Domains

The operating model must define ownership and process for all of the following lifecycles:

1. **RACI ownership** — Who is Responsible, Accountable, Consulted, Informed per domain
2. **Review cadence** — Daily (CI), weekly (drift check), monthly (governance board), quarterly (full review)
3. **Change lifecycle** — Propose → Risk score → Review → Approve → Evidence → Deploy → Verify → Archive → Close
4. **CI gate lifecycle** — PR opened → Scanners run → Gates pass/fail → Merge allowed/blocked → Evidence generated
5. **Evidence lifecycle** — Change record opened → Evidence captured → Review completed → Archive filed → Retention enforced
6. **Exception lifecycle** — Drift found → Exception proposed → Risk assessed → Approved/rejected → Expiry set → Review scheduled → Closed
7. **Incident lifecycle** — Detected → Contained → Recovered → Evidence captured → DR template filed → Post-incident review → Lessons updated
8. **Environment lifecycle** — Dev created → Staging promoted → Prod promoted → Decommissioned → Evidence archived
9. **Disaster recovery lifecycle** — Tabletop scheduled → Scenario reviewed → Recovery owner confirmed → DR evidence filed → Lessons fed back
10. **Production readiness lifecycle** — Change proposed → Readiness checklist completed → Go/no-go decided → Approved → Released → Verified
11. **Post-release verification lifecycle** — Gates checked → Evidence filed → Sign-off obtained → Change record closed → Archive updated
12. **Long-term maintenance model** — Quarterly review → Scanner updates → Doc refresh → RACI review → Evidence purge per retention policy → GAP remediation

