## Required Deliverables

### Documentation Files

1. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-final-operating-model.md`**
   - Executive summary of the governance model
   - Relationship to all prior phases (10–22) with links
   - All 12 lifecycle domains described (as above)
   - How the model evolves over time
   - How new services/routes/changes are onboarded to the governance model
   - Maintenance responsibilities
   - What "governance complete" means for any given change

2. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-operating-model-raci.md`**
   - RACI table covering all governance domains:
     - DNS ownership
     - Tunnel runtime ownership
     - Worker route ownership
     - AI Gateway governance
     - Terraform ownership
     - Secret containment
     - CI gate maintenance
     - Risk scoring
     - Environment separation
     - Disaster recovery
     - Production readiness review
     - Post-release verification
     - Evidence archive maintenance
     - Quarterly review coordination
   - Roles (columns): Cloudflare Runtime Owner | DNS Owner | Worker Owner | Terraform Owner | Security Reviewer | Release Approver | Platform Lead
   - Activities (rows): one per governance task
   - Cells: R (Responsible) / A (Accountable) / C (Consulted) / I (Informed) / — (Not involved)
   - Notes column for caveats

3. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-governance-runbook.md`**
   - Step-by-step runbook for routine governance operations:
     - How to run a drift scan (manual, read-only)
     - How to open a change record (Phase 16)
     - How to complete a risk scorecard (Phase 17)
     - How to complete a readiness review (Phase 20)
     - How to file post-release evidence (Phase 21)
     - How to add a drift exception (Phase 15)
     - How to escalate a critical drift item (Phase 15 → Phase 19)
     - How to conduct a DR tabletop (Phase 19)
     - How to run the quarterly review (this phase)
   - All steps labeled: `[READ-ONLY]`, `[MANUAL]`, or `[REQUIRES APPROVAL]`
   - No automated destructive commands
   - Links to relevant phase docs for each section

4. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-quarterly-review-template.md`**
   - Template for the quarterly governance review:
     - Quarter and year
     - Review date
     - Participants (roles, not names)
     - Quorum met? (yes/no)
   - Sections:
     - Governance phase completeness status (Phases 10–23)
     - Open drift items and SLA compliance (Phase 15)
     - Exception register review (Phase 15)
     - Evidence archive health (Phase 16)
     - Scanner index review (Phase 22) — any GAPs to close?
     - RACI changes needed
     - Environment boundary changes needed (Phase 18)
     - DR tabletop scheduled for next quarter? (Phase 19)
     - Governance gaps found (new column: description | priority | owner | target close date)
     - Recommendations for next quarter
     - Sign-off table (per role)

5. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-runtime-governance-summary.md`**
   - Master summary linking all governance phases (10–23)
   - Table: Phase | Title | Branch | Status | Key Documents | Key Scripts | Phase Summary
   - Cumulative governance coverage assessment:
     - DNS: coverage assessment
     - Tunnel: coverage assessment
     - Workers: coverage assessment
     - Terraform: coverage assessment
     - Secrets: coverage assessment
     - CI: coverage assessment
     - Evidence: coverage assessment
     - DR: coverage assessment
     - Environment separation: coverage assessment
     - Risk scoring: coverage assessment
   - Known remaining gaps (if any)
   - Long-term maintenance schedule

6. **`infra/cloudflare/README.md`** *(update — finalize)*
   - Add Phase 23 entry
   - Update master phase table to mark Phases 10–23 as complete
   - Add link to governance summary and operating model

